text: The 2002 British Open Championships was held at the Lambs Squash Club with the later stages held at the National Squash Centre from 7–15 April 2002. Peter Nicol won the title defeating John White in the final. ==Seeds== ==Draw and results== ===Main draw=== ==References== Category:Men's British Open Squash Championships Men's British Open Men's British Open Squash Championship Men's British Open Squash Championship Men's British Open Squash Championship Category:2000s in Manchester Category:Squash competitions in London Category:Sports competitions in Manchester
